1. 15. c. 40. Galliarum: the provinces of Gallia Lugdunensis and Belgica are here meant. To the former belong the Aedui, also the Andecavi and Turoni (c. 41, 1), to the latter the Treveri. The pressure of debt in Gaul is noticed as early as the time of Cicero.
